    "scenes": [
        {
            "id": "s1",
            "bg_color": "#44aade",
            "text": {
                "header": "Overview",
                "body": "<p>The core deliverable of the pre-sale phase is the <b>media plan</b>.</p><p>It’s like the first beats of song. That’s because it's our first opportunity to create a solid impressions. And it's our first chance to recommend strategies to meet their goals. They send out their RFP to multiple publishers, looking to invest in the best media plans. </p><p>That's why we want our media plan to showcase:</p><ul><li>our expertise with our ad product catalog</li><li>our media strategy skills</li><li>the badassery that is you and your pod</li></ul>",
                "class": "align-center-wide"
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "mic",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0,
                        "ease": "Back.easeOut"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "mic",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s2",
            "bg_color": "#1959b3",
            "text": {
                "header": "Who Does What?",
                "body": "<p>Remember! Media plans don't guarantee that clients will run their campaign with us. Media plans are just proposals that we send back to the client. Clients choose us to run their campaigns when we sign an insertion order. </p><p>In this lesson, let's focus on who does what when building a media plan. We'll also highlight the core resources and systems needed in the pre-sale phase.</p>",
                "class": "align-right"
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "mic",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0,
                        "ease": "Back.easeOut"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "mic",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s3",
            "bg_color": "#44aade",
            "text": {
                "header": "Media Planning Roles",
                "body": "<p>Your role might not be as involved in this phase as much as your peers in the other channels. But It’s just as important for you to know, in case your account executives need your support.</p><p class='pt-callout'>Click on each hat to get a list of the media planning responsibilities owned by each role.</p>",
                "class": "align-left"
            },
            "interaction": {
                "name": "cr_mediaplans_s3",
                "id": "cr-mediaplans-s3",
                "type": "clickReveal",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "header": "Account Executive",
                        "body": "<ul><li>Engages Client Services with the RFP</li><li>Develops initial media plan recommendations</li><li>Reviews media plan with the client for RFP alignment</li><li>Sends the media plan to the client</li><li>Sends IO request to account managers</li></ul>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Sales Planner",
                        "body": "<ul><li>Assists account executive to develop initial media plan recommendations, if necessary</li><li>Builds first version of media plan</li><li>Pulls inventory forecasts</li><li>Revises media plan based on client feedback</li><li>Formats media plans using client templates</li></ul>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Account Manager",
                        "body": "<ul><li>Assists account executive to develop initial media plan recommendations, if necessary</li><li>Builds order into Slingshot</li></ul>"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "cr-mediaplans-s3",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "cr-mediaplans-s3 .reveal-item",
                    "type": "staggerFrom",
                    "duration": 0.3,
                    "startTime": 0.8,
                    "staggerOffset": 0.15,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "cr-mediaplans-s3",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "cr-mediaplans-s3 .reveal-item",
                    "type": "staggerTo",
                    "duration": 0.3,
                    "startTime": 0.8,
                    "staggerOffset": 0.15,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s4",
            "bg_color": "#44aade",
            "text": {
                "header": "Teamwork",
                "body": "<p>In a typical month, you might build a few media plans for some huge campaigns. Or you might be working on a ton of smaller campaigns at the same time.</p><p>That's why knowing how your team works together is critical. Teamwork is an important part of making the dream work. Knowing who handles what will help to start building trust between you and your pod. </p>",
                "class": "align-right"
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "solo-bass",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "solo-bass",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s5",
            "bg_color": "#44aade",
            "text": {
                "header": "Third Party Media Plans &<br>Media Buying Systems",
                "body": "<p>Third party media plans are a common ask from clients during the media planning process. <b>Third party media plan templates</b> are also known as agency spec sheets. Many larger agencies might request us to format our media plans with their templates. That's so they can compare media plans across publishers without worrying about formatting issues. They want to make the metrics, products and budgets easy to compare across media plans. </p><p>Clients might also ask us to build media plans right into their own order management system. Just like we use Slingshot to make media planning easy, clients might use their own system too. Some examples of media planning systems they might use include STRATA, MediaOcean and Prisma. </p><p>In your pod, the account executive and sales planner handles both of these tasks. </p>",
                "class": "align-center-wide"
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "mic",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0,
                        "right": "80%",
                        "ease": "Back.easeOut"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "mic",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        
        {
            "id": "s6",
            "bg_color": "#993333",
            "text": {
                "header": "Media Planning Resources",
                "body": "<p>Knowing who handles what task is only half the battle. Lucky for you we have tons of tools and resources to help you develop the best media plans for your clients. </p><p class='pt-callout'>Click on each instrument for more details.</p>",
                "class": "align-left"
            },
            "interaction": {
                "name": "cr_mediaplans_s6",
                "id": "cr-mediaplans-s6",
                "type": "clickReveal",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "header": "Product Guides",
                        "body": "<p><a href='https://pandora.my.salesforce.com/sfc/#workspaceView?selectedWorkspaceId=05840000000HBNZ' target='_blank'>These documents</a> provide features, benefits, advertising objectives and specifications for our products. You can find them in the Salesforce Libraries.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Avails Tool",
                        "body": "<p>Use <a href='http://slingshot/aap/slingshot/forecast' target='_blank'>this tool</a> for quick spot checks of the guaranteed impression inventory. You'll get real-time avails data to help with client conversations.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "YieldEx",
                        "body": "<p>Use <a href='https://pandora.yieldex.com/YieldexUI/' target='_blank'>this tool</a> Use this tool to check non-guaranteed impressions avails for Performance orders. This tool provides availability estimates in DFP’s non-guaranteed inventory using rate and targeting preferences.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Slingshot",
                        "body": "<p>Your <a href='http://slingshot/aap/slingshot/login?next=/slingshot/' target='_blank'>main tool</a> to build media plans. It’s also where you’ll go to pull avails for your entire order. You can even submit pricing approval requests, all in one place.</p>"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "cr-mediaplans-s6",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
