        },
        {
            "id": "s7",
            "bg_color": "#993333",
            "text": {
                "header": "Pandora Media Plan Workflow",
                "body": "<p>The basic workflow for creating an order in Slingshot is pretty straightforward for a performance order. Click on the light bulbs to see the core steps in the process.</p>",
                "class": "align-right"
            },
            "interaction": {
                "name": "cr_mediaplans_s7",
                "id": "cr-mediaplans-s7",
                "type": "clickReveal",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "header": "Step 1: Create Media Plan and Pull Avails in Slingshot",
                        "body": "<p>Account executives and sales planners plan out line items in Slingshot and pull the avails. That's how you figure out the percentage of inventory that's still available. Work with your pod to recommend revisions. Afterwards account executives and sales planners make the appropriate revisions to the media plan.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Step 2: Revise Media Plan and Re-Pull Avails with YieldEx",
                        "body": "<p>Some line items in your plan might not have enough inventory for your budget. Revise these line items and re-pull the impressions using YieldEx. You might need to revise your media plan a few times. </p><p>Afterwards, the account executive sends it to the client. Media plan revisions can also occur after client feedback.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Step 3: Recheck Avails after getting all Insertion Order signatures ",
                        "body": "<p>After everyone's signed the insertion order, sales planners and account managers may need to recheck impression inventory. This is to make sure that the inventory is still available.</p>"
                    }
                ]
            },
